cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS

This paper proposes a method to compress Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) by representing weight parameters based on Tensor Train (TT) format. The paper focuses on evaluating the proposed method on sequence classification and prediction tasks, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions using the proposed method for image classification tasks, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves reducing the number of parameters in RNNs, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
